last-name>Li</last-name><first-name>Jian-Jun</first-name><address><city>Shenzhen CIty</city><country>CN</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties><assignees><assignee><addressbook><orgname>Shenzhen Super Perfect Optics LTD.</orgname><role>03</role><address><city>Shenzhen City</city><country>CN</country></address></addressbook></assignee></assignees></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">The present disclosure provides a liquid crystal lens, a controlling method thereof and a 3D display using the same. The liquid crystal lens includes a pair of electrode structures which are arranged apart from each other; and a liquid crystal layer which is arranged between the pair of electrode structures and includes a plurality of liquid crystal molecules aligned in an initial aligning direction in which the liquid crystal layer has a non-lens effect. The pair of electrode structures are arranged to generate a first electric field which is used to change aligning directions of the liquid crystal molecules to make the liquid crystal layer have a lens effect. The pair of electrode structures are further arranged to generate a second electric field which is used to make the liquid crystal molecules revert to the initial aligning direction.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>